article.headline: North Texas 86, Florida Atlantic 69
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Eric Tramiel had 17 points as five North Texas players scored in double figures in an 86-69 victory against Florida Atlantic on Thursday night. Tristan Thompson had 16 points, George Odufuwa 14, Alzee Williams 12 and Shannon Shorter 10 for the Mean Green (14-8, 7-5 Sun Belt). Greg Gantt had 18 points and Raymond Taylor 14 for Florida Atlantic (12-11, 8-4), which had a five-game winning streak snapped. Odufuwa had nine rebounds. With the score tied at 9-9 midway through the first half, North Texas scored the game's next 11 points and maintained control the rest of the way.
